  "notes": [
    "D-029 knuckles: each RS00 (\u00d860) is housed in a \u00d866 bulbous stone knuckle at its joint (design wall 3.0mm >= 2.4 req).",
    "SCALE CONFLICT (honest): a movie-proportion leg spans only ~66mm but 3 non-overlapping \u00d866 knuckles would need ~198mm of length, so the three RS00 knuckles necessarily MERGE into one continuous knobbly stone limb rather than three balls on slender links. This is the real tension between D-028 '15x RS00' and the fixed 272mm movie size; the knobbly rock-crab result actually suits an Eridian but the 'slender segment between joints' reads only on the outermost (tibia) link.",
    "Hands are the REAL grip_hand.stl (palm+3 fingers+crown), seated at each tip in the standing pose. They are a separate multi-piece print assembly (rocky/cad/parts/grip_*.py), not fused into the tibia."
  ],
